    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The switch variable must be an integer or character type.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Case labels must be constants of constant expressions.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Case labels must be unique. No two labels can have the same value.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Case labels must end with a colon.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The break statement transfers the program control out of the switch block.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The break statement is optional. When the break is not written in any ‘case’ then the statements following the next case are also executed until the ‘break’ is not found.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The default case is optional. If present, it will be executed when the match with any ‘case’ is not found.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`There can be at most one default label.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The default may be placed any where but generally written at the end.`}</li>
